feat(live-run): Tier-1 agent trace viewer at /runs/:runId

Ships the foundation for "scaffold runs live on our own site with
full agent trace telemetry" -- the LangSmith / Arize AX / Convex Chef
pattern the user called out. Tier 1 is the playback / replay
experience: every scripted step renders as a real Convex row and
the /runs/:runId page subscribes in real time. Tier 2 (actual
sandboxed LLM exec) and Tier 3 (BYOK + real evaluators) are
designed-for and documented in the ADR, not shipped yet.

## Architecture

See docs/LIVE_RUN_AND_TRACE_ADR.md for the full plan. Summary:

  scaffold's observability.py    attrition web app
            |                             |
            |  POST /http/attritionTrace  |
            |  {event, run_id, ...}       |
            |---------------------------->|
            |                             |
            |                             |  mutation: agentTrace.recordSpan
            |                             |  -> agentTraceSpans insert
            |                             |  -> agentRuns patch totals
            |                             |
            |                             |  useQuery(listSpansForRun)
            |                             |  -> /runs/:runId re-renders

## Data model (convex/domains/daas/schema.ts)

  agentRuns (
    runId, sessionSlug?, runtimeLane, driverRuntime, mode,
    status, startedAt, finishedAt?, input, finalOutput?,
    totalCostUsd, totalInputTokens, totalOutputTokens,
    totalSpans, errorMessage?
  )

  agentTraceSpans (
    runId, spanId, parentSpanId?, kind, name,
    startedAt, finishedAt?, inputJson, outputJson,
    inputTokens?, outputTokens?, costUsd?,
    modelLabel?, promptHash?, errorMessage?
  )

6 new indexes: by_runId, by_sessionSlug_startedAt,
by_status_startedAt, by_runId_startedAt, by_runId_kind,
by_parentSpanId. Both tables use string enums (not v.union) for
forward-compat on span kind + run status.

## Domain (convex/domains/daas/agentTrace.ts)

Five functions, all with BOUND / HONEST_STATUS / DETERMINISTIC
invariants per .claude/rules/agentic_reliability.md:

  startRun           mutation. Idempotent by runId so a flaky
                     network can retry without duplicating runs.
  recordSpan         mutation. Idempotent by (runId, spanId).
                     Patches agentRuns denormalized totals only
                     on first insert; re-records patch in place.
                     Truncates inputJson/outputJson to 8KB.
  finishRun          mutation. Bounded status enum (complete|
                     failed). Refuses status="running".
  listSpansForRun    query. Capped at MAX_SPANS_PER_RUN=500,
                     ordered by startedAt ascending.
  getRun             query. Header metadata for the run page.

Bounded: input 4KB, output 8KB, 500 spans per run max.

## HTTP webhook (convex/http.ts)

POST /http/attritionTrace accepts three event types:
  run_start   -> agentTrace.startRun
  span        -> agentTrace.recordSpan
  run_end     -> agentTrace.finishRun

CORS-permissive so scaffolds running on localhost can POST without
a preflight dance. BOUND_READ caps payloads at 32KB.

## Frontend (frontend/src/pages/Run.tsx)

Step-card timeline at /runs/:runId, real-time Convex subscription.
Design borrowed from LangSmith (hierarchical span list, expandable
detail) and Arize AX (filter chips + metadata pills). Every card:

  Left:  kind pill (META/LLM/TOOL/COMPACT/HANDOFF/WAIT), accent
         color per kind (purple/green/cyan/amber/terracotta/grey)
  Middle: time offset from first span, name
  Right:  one-line summary (model + tokens + cost + duration)
  Expand: input JSON, output JSON, metadata pills (model, tokens,
          cost, parent span), error message if failed

Filter chips: all | llm | tool | errors -- counts per filter shown
inline. Shareable-link footer shows current URL for copy-paste.

Error + loading + not-found states all have dedicated cards.

## PreviewTab recorder (frontend/src/components/PreviewTab.tsx)

Added "record live trace" button that walks the script, POSTs real
Convex mutations for each line, then navigates to /runs/:runId.
Each script line becomes a typed span with:
  - $ cmd               -> META run_start
  - [runner]            -> META runner.init
  - [orchestrator] plan -> LLM (claude-sonnet-4.6, realistic
                           tokens + cost)
  - [worker_X]          -> HANDOFF
  - [mock] tool         -> TOOL
  - [orchestrator] compact -> COMPACT
  - [turn N]            -> LLM
  - [graph] / [Runner]  -> TOOL / LLM per lane
  - checkmark line      -> META run_end

Popup-safe: tries window.open, falls back to same-tab navigation
if Chrome's popup blocker is active.

## Offset display fix (Run.tsx)

First ship showed +116580ms offsets on all spans -- clock-skew
artifact between browser Date.now() and Convex server Date.now().
Fixed by using the FIRST span's startedAt as the relative baseline
rather than run.startedAt. Offsets now read +0ms -> +400ms ->
+1.05s -> +4.25s as expected.

## Route registered

/runs/:runId -> ErrorBoundary-wrapped Run page. Unknown runId
shows a NotFoundCard with link back to /. Route in main.tsx
sits next to /next-steps/:slug so 5-checkpoint vocabulary is
consistent.

## Verified end-to-end on prod

  1. Visit /build/demo-retail-ops
  2. Click "Preview" tab
  3. Click "record live trace ->" button
  4. Browser navigates to /runs/<random-id>
  5. See 12 spans rendered: META run_start, META runner.init x2,
     LLM orchestrator.plan (claude-sonnet-4.6, 420 in / 180 out,
     $0.0026, 600ms), 3 HANDOFF, 3 TOOL, 1 COMPACT, META run_end
  6. Filter chips update counts (ALL=12, LLM=1, TOOL=3, ERRORS=0)
  7. Expand LLM span -> see input JSON, output JSON, metadata
     pills (model, in tokens, out tokens, cost)
  8. Shareable link displayed in footer

Zero console errors during the full flow.

## What this earns

- Demo to an investor without leaving our site: they click one
  button, they see spans populating in real time, they can filter
  by kind, they can expand to see per-step detail. That's the
  Convex Chef / LangSmith / Arize AX bar we said we needed to hit.
- The UX is already correct for Tier 2 (real sandbox exec) and
  Tier 3 (BYOK real LLM). Only the data source changes -- same
  schema, same UI, same shareable URL.
- The schema supports nested spans (parentSpanId), so when Tier 2
  ships, orchestrator-worker runs render as nested cards.
- scaffoldPings (NextSteps webhook) + agentTraceSpans (trace
  webhook) sit side by side, both emittable from the same
  observability.py in the scaffold.

## Explicit non-goals for this cycle

- Actual sandboxed LLM execution (Tier 2 next cycle)
- BYOK UI (Tier 3 cycle after)
- User-editable evaluators (Arize-AX-style -- future)
- Streaming token rendering mid-LLM-call (needs SSE)
- Auth-gated private runs (unguessable UUID for now)

